* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈfɜːmətɪv/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/əˈfɝmətɪv/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-affirmative.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# pertaining to [[truth]]; asserting that something ''is''; [[affirm]]ing
#: ''an '''affirmative''' answer''
# pertaining to any [[assertion]] or active [[confirmation]] that favors a particular result
# [[positive]]
#: ''an '''affirmative''' vote''
# Confirmative; ratifying.
#: ''an act '''affirmative''' of common law''
# [[dogmatic]]
#* Berkeley
#*: Lysicles was a little disconcerted by the '''affirmative''' air of Crito.
# {{lb|en|logic}} Expressing the [[agreement]] of the two [[term]]s of a [[proposition]].
# {{lb|en|algebra}} [[positive]]; not [[negative]]

